 President Muhammadu Buhari has announced that a phased and gradual easing of the Covid-19 lockdown in Abuja, Lagos and Ogun states, will commence on Monday, 4th May 2020 at 9am. Selected businesses, according to him, can open between 9am and 6pm, while there will be an overnight curfew from 8pm to 6am. The President said this during his nationwide broadcast on the next phase of action to contain the spread of COVID-19 in the country on Monday. He, however, said the revised guidelines would not apply to Kano State. Details later. 